Coaxial cable type may have either: BNC or F-Type connectors; 
UTP or STP cable types may have: RJ-11 or RJ-45 (8P8C) connectors;
Fiber Optic cable types may have: LC, ST, SC, MT-RJ connectors;

SFP is a transceiver tpye, a removable module that enables connectivity between a device and a cable.


